2. About the App

2.1 The App is enables users to operate their own bitcoin wallet, by storing bitcoin directly onto the phone running the App. Bitcoin can be sent between the App wallet and the wallets of other App users or to any other bitcoin address.

2.2 The App enables users to make bitcoin transactions. KnC is not a money transmitter or a money services business.

2.3 The App is a compilation of two pieces of software to form what is called an ‘aggregate’.

2.4 The first piece of software constituting the aggregate was developed by Andreas Schildbach. It is a bitcoin wallet for android devices (the “Core Software”). The Core Software is licensed to us under the GNU General Public License v.3 and you are permitted to use the Core Software in accordance with the terms of that license. You can find out more about the Core Software at https://github.com/schildbach/bitcoin-wallet.

2.5 The second piece of software constituting the aggregate (the “KnC Software”)_was developed by KnC. You are permitted to use the KnC Software in accordance with this EULA.

2.6 Where this EULA contradicts the rights in the Core Software licensed under the GNU General Public License v.3, the terms of the GNU General Public License v.3 will prevail in respect of the contradictory part only.

2.7 The privacy policy is in an important document which governs our use of the personal and anonymous data that we obtain from your use of the KnC Software. We only use this data in accordance with our privacy policy.

3. About Bitcoin

3.1 Bitcoins may not be appropriate for everyone. Before making use of bitcoin you should learn about them to ensure they are appropriate for you. As with all currencies, there are some risks associated with using bitcoin. Some of the risks particular to bitcoin include:

3.1.1 Loss of bitcoin due to hardware malfunction – if the phone running the App breaks, you could lose the bitcoin stored on that phone;

3.1.2 Currency fluctuation - the price of bitcoin may fall sharply and may even fall to zero;

3.1.3 Bitcoin transactions may be unconfirmed for a period of time. Although very unlikely, some bitcoin transactions may never be confirmed - bitcoin transactions which are unconfirmed are not completed;

3.1.4 Bitcoin transactions are irreversible - if you send bitcoin to the wrong person, you may be unable to recover those bitcoin;

3.1.5 Bitcoin may be lost if you lose or forget any PINs or passwords necessary to access and spend those bitcoin;

3.1.6 Unknown technical defects inherent in bitcoin; and

3.1.7 New regulation which impacts on bitcoin use.

3.2 By agreeing to this EULA or by using the KnC Software, you are indicating your acceptance of the risks associated with bitcoin.

4. User Accounts

4.1 By downloading or using the KnC Software, you confirm that you are either over 18 years of age, or if you are under 18 years old, that you are 13 years of age or older and you have obtained your parent or guardian’s consent to download, and use the KnC Software.

4.2 When you run the App for the first time, a wallet will be created and paired with your phone number. Other users of the App will be able to send bitcoin to this wallet by using your phone number.

4.3 In accordance with our privacy policy, we will remotely store your phone number and other information necessary to enable people to send bitcoin to you.

4.4 When the wallet is created, we will also allocate you with a corresponding “Private Key”. The Private Key enables any bitcoin sent to the App wallet to be spent. For security reasons, we do not keep a backup of your Private Key.

4.5 IF YOUR PRIVATE KEYS ARE LOST OR DELETED, YOU WILL BE UNABLE TO SPEND THE BITCOIN STORED IN THE APP. More information on how you can backup your own Private Key is set out below.

4.6 You have the option to use a PIN to secure access to the App. If you activate the PIN, it will be required to spend any stored bitcoin.

4.7 Your PIN is personal to you and must not be disclosed to any other person. We are entitled to assume that any use of the App is made by you. You are solely responsible and liable for any use of the App.

4.8 IT IS UP TO YOU TO TAKE WHATEVER SECURITY MEASURES YOU THINK NECESSARY TO ENSURE THAT YOUR PIN AND YOUR PHONE ARE SECURE. WE ARE NOT LIABLE FOR ANY IMPROPER USE OF THE APP OR YOUR PIN BY YOU OR ANY OTHER PERSON. IF YOU THINK ANY OTHER PERSON KNOWS YOUR PIN, OR THAT YOUR PHONE HAS BEEN USED OR ACCESSED BY ANY OTHER PERSON WITHOUT YOUR PERMISSION, YOU MUST CHANGE YOUR PIN AND INFORM US IMMEDIATELY.

